                        <h3 class="panel-title">About SMETA</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel-body">
                        Social Media Emotional Tendency Analysis(SMETA) seeks to analyze the way the emotional bias in various social media posts change in accordance with time. The two sentiments 
                        visualized are neutrality and positivity, where neutrality shows how strong an emotional response is while positivity shows how happy the emotion is. Twitter posts are taken 
                        from the streaming API which are then processed through Text-Processing sentiment analysis and displayed on the front-end. SMETA allows chances for integration with existing 
                        projects such as the Hedonometer as well as to build off of. As our personal limitations for the product largely had to do with availability of data from multiple social media
                         services and database affordability, keeping the project open to change is a main focus.

                    </div>
